{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":468,"text":"What I'd like to do today is talk\nabout one of my favorite subjects,"},{"time":4857,"text":"and that is the neuroscience of sleep."}]},{"cues":[{"time":8542,"text":"Now, there is a sound --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":11120,"text":"(Alarm clock)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":13150,"text":"Ah, it worked!"},{"time":15190,"text":"A sound that is desperately\nfamiliar to most of us,"},{"time":18792,"text":"and of course it's the sound\nof the alarm clock."},{"time":21156,"text":"And what that truly ghastly,\nawful sound does"},{"time":24347,"text":"is stop the single most important\nbehavioral experience"},{"time":29738,"text":"that we have, and that's sleep."},{"time":32695,"text":"If you're an average sort of person,"},{"time":36010,"text":"36 percent of your life\nwill be spent asleep,"},{"time":40433,"text":"which means that if you live to 90,"},{"time":42668,"text":"then 32 years will have\nbeen spent entirely asleep."}]},{"cues":[{"time":49587,"text":"Now what that 32 years is telling us\nis that sleep at some level is important."},{"time":54857,"text":"And yet, for most of us,\nwe don't give sleep a second thought."},{"time":57836,"text":"We throw it away."},{"time":59669,"text":"We really just don't think about sleep."},{"time":62921,"text":"And so what I'd like to do today\nis change your views,"},{"time":66540,"text":"change your ideas\nand your thoughts about sleep."},{"time":69739,"text":"And the journey\nthat I want to take you on,"},{"time":72130,"text":"we need to start by going back in time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":76706,"text":"\"Enjoy the honey-heavy dew of slumber.\""},{"time":81266,"text":"Any ideas who said that?"},{"time":84640,"text":"Shakespeare's Julius Caesar."},{"time":86999,"text":"Yes, let me give you a few more quotes."},{"time":90621,"text":"\"O sleep, O gentle sleep,\nnature's soft nurse,"},{"time":94595,"text":"how have I frighted thee?\""},{"time":95944,"text":"Shakespeare again, from --\nI won't say it --"},{"time":98541,"text":"the Scottish play."}]},{"cues":[{"time":99939,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":102577,"text":"From the same time:"},{"time":103831,"text":"\"Sleep is the golden chain\nthat ties health and our bodies together.\""},{"time":108060,"text":"Extremely prophetic, by Thomas Dekker,\nanother Elizabethan dramatist."}]},{"cues":[{"time":112636,"text":"But if we jump forward 400 years,"},{"time":115678,"text":"the tone about sleep changes somewhat."},{"time":119043,"text":"This is from Thomas Edison,\nfrom the beginning of the 20th century:"},{"time":122238,"text":"\"Sleep is a criminal waste of time\nand a heritage from our cave days.\""},{"time":125898,"text":"Bang!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":127105,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":129673,"text":"And if we also jump into the 1980s,\nsome of you may remember"},{"time":134789,"text":"that Margaret Thatcher\nwas reported to have said,"},{"time":137163,"text":"\"Sleep is for wimps.\""},{"time":138628,"text":"And of course the infamous --\nwhat was his name? --"},{"time":141523,"text":"the infamous Gordon Gekko\nfrom \"Wall Street\" said,"},{"time":143985,"text":"\"Money never sleeps.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":146460,"text":"What do we do in the 20th\ncentury about sleep?"},{"time":149140,"text":"Well, of course, we use\nThomas Edison's light bulb"},{"time":152505,"text":"to invade the night,\nand we occupied the dark,"},{"time":155351,"text":"and in the process of this occupation,"},{"time":158136,"text":"we've treated sleep as an illness, almost."},{"time":160741,"text":"We've treated it as an enemy."},{"time":163677,"text":"At most now, I suppose,\nwe tolerate the need for sleep,"},{"time":169068,"text":"and at worst perhaps\nmany of us think of sleep"},{"time":171259,"text":"as an illness that needs\nsome sort of a cure."},{"time":174247,"text":"And our ignorance about sleep\nis really quite profound."},{"time":178307,"text":"Why is it? Why do we abandon\nsleep in our thoughts?"},{"time":181668,"text":"Well, it's because you don't do anything\nmuch while you're asleep, it seems."},{"time":186008,"text":"You don't eat. You don't drink."},{"time":189513,"text":"And you don't have sex."},{"time":190814,"text":"Well, most of us anyway."},{"time":192242,"text":"And so, therefore it's --"},{"time":194070,"text":"Sorry."},{"time":196032,"text":"It's a complete waste of time, right?"},{"time":198292,"text":"Wrong."},{"time":199689,"text":"Actually, sleep is an incredibly\nimportant part of our biology,"},{"time":203512,"text":"and neuroscientists\nare beginning to explain"},{"time":206080,"text":"why it's so very important."},{"time":208547,"text":"So let's move to the brain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":211383,"text":"Now, here we have a brain."},{"time":216140,"text":"This is donated by a social scientist,"},{"time":219985,"text":"and they said they didn't know what\nit was or indeed, how to use it, so --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":223604,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":226582,"text":"Sorry."},{"time":228714,"text":"So I borrowed it."},{"time":230318,"text":"I don't think they noticed. OK."}]},{"cues":[{"time":232030,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":234618,"text":"The point I'm trying to make\nis that when you're asleep,"},{"time":237815,"text":"this thing doesn't shut down."},{"time":239583,"text":"In fact, some areas of the brain\nare actually more active"},{"time":242289,"text":"during the sleep state\nthan during the wake state."},{"time":245439,"text":"The other thing that's really\nimportant about sleep"},{"time":247869,"text":"is that it doesn't arise from a single\nstructure within the brain,"},{"time":251019,"text":"but is to some extent a network property."},{"time":253200,"text":"If we flip the brain on its back --"},{"time":255656,"text":"I love this little bit\nof spinal cord here --"},{"time":258668,"text":"this bit here is the hypothalamus,"},{"time":261597,"text":"and right under there is a whole raft\nof interesting structures,"},{"time":265435,"text":"not least the biological clock."},{"time":267040,"text":"The biological clock tells us\nwhen it's good to be up,"},{"time":269679,"text":"when it's good to be asleep,"},{"time":271251,"text":"and what that structure does is interact"},{"time":273203,"text":"with a whole raft of other areas\nwithin the hypothalamus,"},{"time":276445,"text":"the lateral hypothalamus,\nthe ventrolateral preoptic nuclei."},{"time":279289,"text":"All of those combine,"},{"time":280677,"text":"and they send projections\ndown to the brain stem here."},{"time":283888,"text":"The brain stem then projects forward"},{"time":286889,"text":"and bathes the cortex,\nthis wonderfully wrinkly bit over here,"},{"time":290958,"text":"with neurotransmitters that keep us awake"},{"time":293416,"text":"and essentially provide us\nwith our consciousness."},{"time":296054,"text":"So sleep arises from a whole raft"},{"time":298794,"text":"of different interactions\nwithin the brain,"},{"time":300897,"text":"and essentially,\nsleep is turned on and off"},{"time":303090,"text":"as a result of a range\nof interactions in here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":306035,"text":"OK. So where have we got to?"},{"time":307924,"text":"We've said that sleep is complicated"},{"time":311474,"text":"and it takes 32 years of our life."},{"time":316188,"text":"But what I haven't explained\nis what sleep is about."},{"time":319251,"text":"So why do we sleep?"},{"time":321401,"text":"And it won't surprise\nany of you that, of course,"},{"time":323719,"text":"as scientists, we don't have a consensus."},{"time":325711,"text":"There are dozens of different ideas\nabout why we sleep,"},{"time":329009,"text":"and I'm going to outline three of those."}]},{"cues":[{"time":331517,"text":"The first is sort of the restoration idea,"},{"time":334240,"text":"and it's somewhat intuitive."},{"time":336110,"text":"Essentially, all the stuff\nwe've burned up during the day,"},{"time":338900,"text":"we restore, we replace,\nwe rebuild during the night."},{"time":342160,"text":"And indeed, as an explanation,\nit goes back to Aristotle,"},{"time":345636,"text":"so that's what -- 2,300 years ago."},{"time":347837,"text":"It's gone in and out of fashion."},{"time":349458,"text":"It's fashionable at the moment"},{"time":350927,"text":"because what's been shown\nis that within the brain,"},{"time":353344,"text":"a whole raft of genes have been shown\nto be turned on only during sleep,"},{"time":358010,"text":"and those genes are associated\nwith restoration and metabolic pathways."},{"time":362333,"text":"So there's good evidence\nfor the whole restoration hypothesis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":366436,"text":"What about energy conservation?"},{"time":368428,"text":"Again, perhaps intuitive."},{"time":371764,"text":"You essentially sleep to save calories."},{"time":374488,"text":"Now, when you do the sums,\nthough, it doesn't really pan out."},{"time":377958,"text":"If you compare an individual\nwho has slept at night,"},{"time":382302,"text":"or stayed awake\nand hasn't moved very much,"},{"time":386033,"text":"the energy saving of sleeping\nis about 110 calories a night."},{"time":390601,"text":"Now, that's the equivalent\nof a hot dog bun."},{"time":393934,"text":"Now, I would say that a hot dog bun"},{"time":397518,"text":"is kind of a meager return"},{"time":399335,"text":"for such a complicated\nand demanding behavior as sleep."},{"time":402454,"text":"So I'm less convinced\nby the energy conservation idea."}]},{"cues":[{"time":406397,"text":"But the third idea I'm quite attracted to,"},{"time":408621,"text":"which is brain processing\nand memory consolidation."},{"time":412100,"text":"What we know is that,\nif after you've tried to learn a task,"},{"time":416002,"text":"and you sleep-deprive individuals,"},{"time":417836,"text":"the ability to learn that task is smashed."},{"time":420401,"text":"It's really hugely attenuated."},{"time":423481,"text":"So sleep and memory consolidation\nis also very important."},{"time":426545,"text":"However, it's not just\nthe laying down of memory"},{"time":429070,"text":"and recalling it."},{"time":430664,"text":"What's turned out to be really exciting"},{"time":433024,"text":"is that our ability to come up\nwith novel solutions to complex problems"},{"time":437587,"text":"is hugely enhanced by a night of sleep."},{"time":440029,"text":"In fact, it's been estimated\nto give us a threefold advantage."},{"time":443456,"text":"Sleeping at night enhances our creativity."},{"time":446123,"text":"And what seems to be going on\nis that, in the brain,"},{"time":449003,"text":"those neural connections\nthat are important,"},{"time":451580,"text":"those synaptic connections\nthat are important,"},{"time":453781,"text":"are linked and strengthened,"},{"time":455312,"text":"while those that are less important\ntend to fade away and be less important."}]},{"cues":[{"time":460218,"text":"OK."},{"time":461393,"text":"So we've had three explanations\nfor why we might sleep,"},{"time":464432,"text":"and I think the important thing to realize\nis that the details will vary,"},{"time":468110,"text":"and it's probable we sleep\nfor multiple different reasons."},{"time":471235,"text":"But sleep is not an indulgence."},{"time":474385,"text":"It's not some sort of thing that we can\ntake on board rather casually."},{"time":479040,"text":"I think that sleep was once\nlikened to an upgrade"},{"time":482907,"text":"from economy to business class,\nyou know, the equivalent of."},{"time":485955,"text":"It's not even an upgrade\nfrom economy to first class."},{"time":489748,"text":"The critical thing to realize is that\nif you don't sleep,"},{"time":494889,"text":"you don't fly."},{"time":496260,"text":"Essentially, you never get there."},{"time":498233,"text":"And what's extraordinary\nabout much of our society these days"},{"time":501542,"text":"is that we are desperately sleep-deprived."}]},{"cues":[{"time":504615,"text":"So let's now look at sleep deprivation."},{"time":507298,"text":"Huge sectors of society\nare sleep-deprived,"},{"time":510012,"text":"and let's look at our sleep-o-meter."},{"time":512764,"text":"So in the 1950s, good data\nsuggests that most of us"},{"time":516125,"text":"were getting around eight hours\nof sleep a night."},{"time":519490,"text":"Nowadays, we sleep one and a half\nto two hours less every night,"},{"time":523368,"text":"so we're in the six-and-a-half-hours\nevery-night league."},{"time":527686,"text":"For teenagers, it's worse, much worse."},{"time":530644,"text":"They need nine hours\nfor full brain performance,"},{"time":533626,"text":"and many of them, on a school night,\nare only getting five hours of sleep."},{"time":537293,"text":"It's simply not enough."},{"time":538945,"text":"If we think about other sectors\nof society -- the aged;"},{"time":542013,"text":"if you are aged, then your ability\nto sleep in a single block"},{"time":546452,"text":"is somewhat disrupted,\nand many sleep, again,"},{"time":549040,"text":"less than five hours a night."}]},{"cues":[{"time":550792,"text":"Shift work."},{"time":551973,"text":"Shift work is extraordinary,"},{"time":553528,"text":"perhaps 20 percent\nof the working population,"},{"time":556036,"text":"and the body clock does not shift\nto the demands of working at night."},{"time":560030,"text":"It's locked onto the same\nlight-dark cycle as the rest of us."},{"time":563224,"text":"So when the poor old\nshift worker is going home"},{"time":565459,"text":"to try and sleep during the day,\ndesperately tired,"},{"time":567960,"text":"the body clock is saying,\n\"Wake up. This is the time to be awake.\""},{"time":571100,"text":"So the quality of sleep\nthat you get as a night shift worker"},{"time":574180,"text":"is usually very poor,\nagain in that sort of five-hour region."},{"time":577563,"text":"And then, of course, tens of millions\nof people suffer from jet lag."},{"time":581100,"text":"So who here has jet lag?"},{"time":584389,"text":"Well, my goodness gracious."},{"time":586365,"text":"Well, thank you very much\nindeed for not falling asleep,"},{"time":589195,"text":"because that's what your brain is craving."}]},{"cues":[{"time":591893,"text":"One of the things that the brain does\nis indulge in micro-sleeps,"},{"time":597231,"text":"this involuntary falling asleep,"},{"time":599000,"text":"and you have essentially\nno control over it."},{"time":601237,"text":"Now, micro-sleeps can be sort\nof somewhat embarrassing,"},{"time":604020,"text":"but they can also be deadly."},{"time":606020,"text":"It's been estimated\nthat 31 percent of drivers"},{"time":609699,"text":"will fall asleep at the wheel\nat least once in their life,"},{"time":614005,"text":"and in the US, the statistics\nare pretty good:"},{"time":616195,"text":"100,000 accidents on the freeway\nhave been associated with tiredness,"},{"time":621416,"text":"loss of vigilance, and falling asleep --\na hundred thousand a year."},{"time":624604,"text":"It's extraordinary."},{"time":625786,"text":"At another level of terror,"},{"time":627875,"text":"we dip into the tragic\naccidents at Chernobyl"},{"time":631477,"text":"and indeed the space shuttle Challenger,"},{"time":633624,"text":"which was so tragically lost."},{"time":635577,"text":"And in the investigations\nthat followed those disasters,"},{"time":639002,"text":"poor judgment as a result\nof extended shift work"},{"time":642020,"text":"and loss of vigilance and tiredness"},{"time":644326,"text":"was attributed to a big chunk\nof those disasters."},{"time":650408,"text":"When you're tired and you lack sleep,"},{"time":652511,"text":"you have poor memory,\nyou have poor creativity,"},{"time":656156,"text":"you have increased impulsiveness,"},{"time":658287,"text":"and you have overall poor judgment."},{"time":660914,"text":"But my friends,\nit's so much worse than that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":664025,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":666096,"text":"If you are a tired brain,"},{"time":668080,"text":"the brain is craving things to wake it up."},{"time":671040,"text":"So drugs, stimulants."},{"time":673230,"text":"Caffeine represents\nthe stimulant of choice"},{"time":676924,"text":"across much of the Western world."},{"time":678528,"text":"Much of the day is fueled by caffeine,"},{"time":680575,"text":"and if you're a really naughty\ntired brain, nicotine."},{"time":683613,"text":"Of course, you're fueling the waking state\nwith these stimulants,"},{"time":686930,"text":"and then, of course, it gets\nto 11 o'clock at night,"},{"time":689390,"text":"and the brain says to itself,"},{"time":690802,"text":"\"Actually, I need\nto be asleep fairly shortly."},{"time":692988,"text":"What do we do about that\nwhen I'm feeling completely wired?\""},{"time":695881,"text":"Well, of course,\nyou then resort to alcohol."},{"time":698765,"text":"Now alcohol, short-term,\nyou know, once or twice,"},{"time":702020,"text":"to use to mildly sedate you,\ncan be very useful."},{"time":704795,"text":"It can actually ease the sleep transition."},{"time":707675,"text":"But what you must be so aware of\nis that alcohol doesn't provide sleep."},{"time":712947,"text":"A biological mimic for sleep,"},{"time":714438,"text":"it sedates you."},{"time":715669,"text":"So it actually harms\nsome of the neural processing"},{"time":719058,"text":"that's going on during memory\nconsolidation and memory recall."},{"time":722010,"text":"So it's a short-term acute measure,"},{"time":724198,"text":"but for goodness sake,"},{"time":725380,"text":"don't become addicted to alcohol"},{"time":727414,"text":"as a way of getting to sleep every night."}]},{"cues":[{"time":730095,"text":"Another connection\nbetween loss of sleep is weight gain."},{"time":733644,"text":"If you sleep around\nabout five hours or less every night,"},{"time":737263,"text":"then you have a 50 percent\nlikelihood of being obese."},{"time":741132,"text":"What's the connection here?"},{"time":742879,"text":"Well, sleep loss seems to give rise\nto the release of the hormone ghrelin,"},{"time":747267,"text":"the hunger hormone."},{"time":748448,"text":"Ghrelin is released."},{"time":749624,"text":"It gets to the brain."},{"time":751059,"text":"The brain says, \"I need carbohydrates,\""},{"time":753866,"text":"and what it does is seek out carbohydrates\nand particularly sugars."},{"time":757493,"text":"So there's a link between tiredness"},{"time":760208,"text":"and the metabolic predisposition\nfor weight gain: stress."},{"time":763802,"text":"Tired people are massively stressed."},{"time":766890,"text":"And one of the things of stress,\nof course, is loss of memory,"},{"time":770183,"text":"which is what I sort of just then\nhad a little lapse of."},{"time":775140,"text":"But stress is so much more."},{"time":777145,"text":"So, if you're acutely stressed,\nnot a great problem,"},{"time":780319,"text":"but it's sustained stress associated\nwith sleep loss that's the problem."},{"time":784118,"text":"Sustained stress leads\nto suppressed immunity."},{"time":788219,"text":"And so, tired people tend to have\nhigher rates of overall infection,"},{"time":791806,"text":"and there's some very good studies"},{"time":793482,"text":"showing that shift workers, for example,\nhave higher rates of cancer."},{"time":796908,"text":"Increased levels of stress\nthrow glucose into the circulation."},{"time":800756,"text":"Glucose becomes a dominant part\nof the vasculature"},{"time":804798,"text":"and essentially you become\nglucose intolerant."},{"time":807290,"text":"Therefore, diabetes 2."},{"time":809609,"text":"Stress increases cardiovascular disease\nas a result of raising blood pressure."},{"time":815515,"text":"So there's a whole raft of things\nassociated with sleep loss"},{"time":818832,"text":"that are more than just\na mildly impaired brain,"},{"time":822479,"text":"which is where I think most people think\nthat sleep loss resides."}]},{"cues":[{"time":825613,"text":"So at this point in the talk,\nthis is a nice time to think,"},{"time":829020,"text":"\"Well, do you think on the whole\nI'm getting enough sleep?\""},{"time":832234,"text":"So a quick show of hands."},{"time":834012,"text":"Who feels that they're getting\nenough sleep here?"},{"time":837067,"text":"Oh. Well, that's pretty impressive."},{"time":839536,"text":"Good. We'll talk more about that later,\nabout what are your tips."}]},{"cues":[{"time":842639,"text":"So most of us, of course,\nask the question,"},{"time":845059,"text":"\"How do I know whether\nI'm getting enough sleep?\""},{"time":847390,"text":"Well, it's not rocket science."},{"time":848850,"text":"If you need an alarm clock to get\nyou out of bed in the morning,"},{"time":851936,"text":"if you are taking a long time to get up,"},{"time":853997,"text":"if you need lots of stimulants,"},{"time":855552,"text":"if you're grumpy, if you're irritable,"},{"time":857520,"text":"if you're told by your work colleagues\nthat you're looking tired and irritable,"},{"time":861342,"text":"chances are you are sleep-deprived."},{"time":863691,"text":"Listen to them. Listen to yourself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":865824,"text":"What do you do?"},{"time":867291,"text":"Well -- and this is slightly offensive --"},{"time":869348,"text":"sleep for dummies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":870529,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":872673,"text":"Make your bedroom a haven for sleep."},{"time":875482,"text":"The first critical thing is make it\nas dark as you possibly can,"},{"time":879010,"text":"and also make it slightly cool."},{"time":880875,"text":"Very important."},{"time":882051,"text":"Actually, reduce your amount\nof light exposure"},{"time":884981,"text":"at least half an hour\nbefore you go to bed."},{"time":887354,"text":"Light increases levels of alertness\nand will delay sleep."},{"time":890131,"text":"What's the last thing that most of us\ndo before we go to bed?"},{"time":893018,"text":"We stand in a massively lit bathroom,"},{"time":895411,"text":"looking into the mirror\ncleaning our teeth."},{"time":897530,"text":"It's the worst thing we can possibly do\nbefore we go to sleep."},{"time":901109,"text":"Turn off those mobile phones.\nTurn off those computers."},{"time":903836,"text":"Turn off all of those things\nthat are also going to excite the brain."},{"time":908155,"text":"Try not to drink caffeine\ntoo late in the day,"},{"time":910843,"text":"ideally not after lunch."}]},{"cues":[{"time":913715,"text":"Now, we've set about reducing light\nexposure before you go to bed,"},{"time":917040,"text":"but light exposure in the morning"},{"time":918996,"text":"is very good at setting the biological\nclock to the light-dark cycle."},{"time":922311,"text":"So seek out morning light."},{"time":923994,"text":"Basically, listen to yourself."},{"time":926474,"text":"Wind down."},{"time":927650,"text":"Do those sorts of things"},{"time":928836,"text":"that you know are going to ease you off"},{"time":930882,"text":"into the honey-heavy dew of slumber."}]},{"cues":[{"time":934195,"text":"OK."},{"time":935378,"text":"That's some facts. What about some myths?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":937704,"text":"Teenagers are lazy."},{"time":939010,"text":"No. Poor things."},{"time":940898,"text":"They have a biological predisposition\nto go to bed late and get up late,"},{"time":944348,"text":"so give them a break."}]},{"cues":[{"time":945661,"text":"We need eight hours of sleep a night."},{"time":949392,"text":"That's an average."},{"time":950572,"text":"Some people need more.\nSome people need less."},{"time":952864,"text":"And what you need to do\nis listen to your body."},{"time":955101,"text":"Do you need that much or do you need more?"},{"time":957466,"text":"Simple as that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":958866,"text":"Old people need less sleep."},{"time":961010,"text":"Not true."},{"time":962684,"text":"The sleep demands of the aged\ndo not go down."},{"time":965584,"text":"Essentially, sleep fragments\nand becomes less robust,"},{"time":968903,"text":"but sleep requirements do not go down."}]},{"cues":[{"time":971674,"text":"And the fourth myth\nis early to bed, early to rise"},{"time":975603,"text":"makes a man healthy, wealthy and wise."},{"time":978270,"text":"Well, that's wrong\nat so many different levels."}]},{"cues":[{"time":981050,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":983405,"text":"There is no evidence that getting up early\nand going to bed early"},{"time":987944,"text":"gives you more wealth at all."},{"time":989388,"text":"There's no difference\nin socioeconomic status."},{"time":992020,"text":"In my experience,"},{"time":993195,"text":"the only difference between morning\npeople and evening people"},{"time":996104,"text":"is that those people that get up\nin the morning early"},{"time":998629,"text":"are just horribly smug."}]},{"cues":[{"time":999945,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1001240,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1004567,"text":"OK."},{"time":1005743,"text":"So for the last few minutes,"},{"time":1007293,"text":"what I want to do is change gears"},{"time":1009190,"text":"and talk about some really new,\nbreaking areas of neuroscience,"},{"time":1012963,"text":"which is the association\nbetween mental health,"},{"time":1015871,"text":"mental illness and sleep disruption."},{"time":1018189,"text":"We've known for 130 years\nthat in severe mental illness,"},{"time":1022313,"text":"there is always, always sleep disruption,"},{"time":1025621,"text":"but it's been largely ignored."},{"time":1027103,"text":"In the 1970s, when people started\nto think about this again,"},{"time":1029951,"text":"they said, \"Yes, well, of course you have\nsleep disruption in schizophrenia,"},{"time":1033781,"text":"because they're on antipsychotics."},{"time":1035852,"text":"It's the antipsychotics causing\nthe sleep problems,\""},{"time":1038888,"text":"ignoring the fact that\nfor a hundred years previously,"},{"time":1041841,"text":"sleep disruption had been reported\nbefore antipsychotics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1045846,"text":"So what's going on?"},{"time":1047670,"text":"Several groups are studying"},{"time":1050698,"text":"conditions like depression,\nschizophrenia and bipolar"},{"time":1054020,"text":"and what's going on\nin terms of sleep disruption."},{"time":1056770,"text":"We have a big study which we published\nlast year on schizophrenia,"},{"time":1060508,"text":"and the data were quite extraordinary."},{"time":1063981,"text":"In those individuals with schizophrenia,"},{"time":1066957,"text":"much of the time, they were awake\nduring the night phase"},{"time":1070874,"text":"and then they were asleep during the day."},{"time":1073088,"text":"Other groups showed no 24-hour\npatterns whatsoever --"},{"time":1075651,"text":"their sleep was absolutely smashed."},{"time":1077620,"text":"And some had no ability to regulate\ntheir sleep by the light-dark cycle."},{"time":1081808,"text":"They were getting up later and later\nand later and later each night."},{"time":1085074,"text":"It was smashed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1086371,"text":"So what's going on?"},{"time":1088582,"text":"And the really exciting news"},{"time":1090130,"text":"is that mental illness and sleep\nare not simply associated,"},{"time":1095733,"text":"but they are physically linked\nwithin the brain."},{"time":1098471,"text":"The neural networks that predispose\nyou to normal sleep,"},{"time":1101429,"text":"give you normal sleep,"},{"time":1102714,"text":"and those that give you normal\nmental health, are overlapping."},{"time":1106344,"text":"And what's the evidence for that?"},{"time":1108027,"text":"Well, genes that have been shown"},{"time":1110964,"text":"to be very important\nin the generation of normal sleep,"},{"time":1113918,"text":"when mutated, when changed,"},{"time":1115685,"text":"also predispose individuals\nto mental health problems."},{"time":1119041,"text":"And last year, we published a study"},{"time":1121026,"text":"which showed that a gene\nthat's been linked to schizophrenia,"},{"time":1124413,"text":"when mutated, also smashes the sleep."},{"time":1127793,"text":"So we have evidence\nof a genuine mechanistic overlap"},{"time":1131140,"text":"between these two important systems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1133806,"text":"Other work flowed from these studies."},{"time":1135830,"text":"The first was that sleep disruption"},{"time":1139030,"text":"actually precedes certain types\nof mental illness,"},{"time":1142932,"text":"and we've shown that\nin those young individuals"},{"time":1145368,"text":"who are at high risk\nof developing bipolar disorder,"},{"time":1148777,"text":"they already have a sleep abnormality"},{"time":1151294,"text":"prior to any clinical\ndiagnosis of bipolar."},{"time":1155463,"text":"The other bit of data\nwas that sleep disruption"},{"time":1161212,"text":"may actually exacerbate, make worse,\nthe mental illness state."},{"time":1165378,"text":"My colleague Dan Freeman\nhas used a range of agents"},{"time":1168040,"text":"which have stabilized sleep\nand reduced levels of paranoia"},{"time":1171608,"text":"in those individuals by 50 percent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1174189,"text":"So what have we got?"},{"time":1175808,"text":"We've got, in these connections,\nsome really exciting things."},{"time":1181721,"text":"In terms of the neuroscience,"},{"time":1183147,"text":"by understanding these two systems,"},{"time":1184917,"text":"we're really beginning to understand\nhow both sleep and mental illness"},{"time":1188241,"text":"are generated and regulated\nwithin the brain."},{"time":1191128,"text":"The second area\nis that if we can use sleep"},{"time":1194843,"text":"and sleep disruption\nas an early warning signal,"},{"time":1197351,"text":"then we have the chance of going in."},{"time":1199621,"text":"If we know these individuals\nare vulnerable,"},{"time":1202050,"text":"early intervention then becomes possible."},{"time":1204593,"text":"And the third, which I think\nis the most exciting,"},{"time":1207188,"text":"is that we can think\nof the sleep centers within the brain"},{"time":1209990,"text":"as a new therapeutic target."},{"time":1211370,"text":"Stabilize sleep in those individuals\nwho are vulnerable,"},{"time":1214284,"text":"we can certainly make them healthier,"},{"time":1216295,"text":"but also alleviate some of the appalling\nsymptoms of mental illness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1221010,"text":"So let me just finish."},{"time":1222396,"text":"What I started by saying is:\nTake sleep seriously."},{"time":1225687,"text":"Our attitudes toward sleep\nare so very different"},{"time":1228160,"text":"from a pre-industrial age,"},{"time":1229709,"text":"when we were almost wrapped in a duvet."},{"time":1231836,"text":"We used to understand intuitively\nthe importance of sleep."},{"time":1235299,"text":"And this isn't some sort\nof crystal-waving nonsense."},{"time":1238878,"text":"This is a pragmatic response\nto good health."},{"time":1241522,"text":"If you have good sleep,\nit increases your concentration,"},{"time":1244363,"text":"attention, decision-making,\ncreativity, social skills, health."},{"time":1248372,"text":"If you get sleep, it reduces\nyour mood changes, your stress,"},{"time":1252721,"text":"your levels of anger, your impulsivity,"},{"time":1254878,"text":"and your tendency to drink and take drugs."},{"time":1257495,"text":"And we finished by saying"},{"time":1260354,"text":"that an understanding\nof the neuroscience of sleep"},{"time":1263504,"text":"is really informing the way we think"},{"time":1266332,"text":"about some of the causes\nof mental illness,"},{"time":1268866,"text":"and indeed is providing us new ways"},{"time":1270946,"text":"to treat these incredibly\ndebilitating conditions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1275666,"text":"Jim Butcher, the fantasy writer, said,"},{"time":1279500,"text":"\"Sleep is God. Go worship.\""},{"time":1281545,"text":"And I can only recommend\nthat you do the same."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1283776,"text":"Thank you for your attention."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1285228,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}